definitions.definition: The quantity of bread or other baked goods baked at one time.
examples: We made a batch of cookies to take to the party.

definitions.definition: ( by extension ) A quantity of anything produced at one operation.
examples: We poured a bucket of water in at the top, and the ice-maker dispensed a batch of ice-cubes at the bottom.

definitions.definition: A group or collection of things of the same kind, such as a batch of letters or the next batch of business.
( computing ) A set of data to be processed at one time.
examples: The system throttled itself to batches of 50 requests at a time to keep the thread count under control.

definitions.definition: ( UK , dialect , Midlands ) A bread roll .
( Philippines ) A graduating class; school class .
examples: She was the valedictorian of Batch ’73.
